<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb0c05667-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0" identifier="/us/usc/t37/s1013"><num value="1013">§ 1013.</num><heading> Payment of compensation for victims of terrorism</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any benefit or payment pursuant to <ref href="/us/usc/t37/s559">section 559 of this title</ref>, or section 1032 or 1095a or chapter 110 of title 10, shall be paid out of funds available to the Secretary concerned for military personnel.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb0c05668-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/99/399/tVIII/s801/e/1">Pub. L. 99–399, title VIII, § 801(e)(1)</ref>, <date date="1986-08-27">Aug. 27, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/888">100 Stat. 888</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/100/456/dA/tXII/s1233/g/4">Pub. L. 100–456, div. A, title XII, § 1233(g)(4)</ref>, <date date="1988-09-29">Sept. 29, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/2058">102 Stat. 2058</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/101/510/dA/tXIV/s1484/h/6">Pub. L. 101–510, div. A, title XIV, § 1484(h)(6)</ref>, <date date="1990-11-05">Nov. 5, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/1718">104 Stat. 1718</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb0c05669-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb0c0566a-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idb0c0566b-2930-11f1-a69d-9cbca84c43f0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Another section 1013 was renumbered <ref href="/us/usc/t37/s1014">section 1014 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
